special database all on its own.

403
00:20:54,250 --> 00:20:56,625
You showed her that.
When you took her around

404
00:20:56,708 --> 00:20:59,125
Akihabara and let her see
how much it meant to you.

405
00:20:59,208 --> 00:21:00,708
[gasps]

406
00:21:00,791 --> 00:21:02,125
[PROFESSOR]
Pyuko must have determined

407
00:21:02,208 --> 00:21:04,875
her action would protect that.
By saving this place,

408
00:21:04,958 --> 00:21:07,750
she was saving your
most precious data.

409
00:21:07,833 --> 00:21:10,416
She's gone, but as long
as you remember her,

410
00:21:10,500 --> 00:21:13,541
Pyuko will live on, in your
own stored memories.

411
00:21:13,625 --> 00:21:14,791
[TAMOTSU sighs]

412
00:21:14,875 --> 00:21:17,250
[PROFESSOR] So take good
care of that data, okay?

413
00:21:17,333 --> 00:21:18,833
She's counting on you.

414
00:21:18,916 --> 00:21:21,041
[TAMOTSU grunts]
Pyuko.

415
00:21:53,708 --> 00:21:58,666
♪


416
00:23:24,666 --> 00:23:27,041
Come on. The streets
won't patrol themselves.

417
00:23:27,125 --> 00:23:29,625
[TAMOTSU grunts]

418
00:23:29,708 --> 00:23:31,458
Yeah, I'm coming.

419
00:23:38,750 --> 00:23:40,291
[TAMOTSU chuckles]

420
00:23:44,291 --> 00:23:46,458
